President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India to congratulate India on its 70 years of freedom and independence. They discussed enhancing peace and stability in the Indo-Pacific region by establishing a new ministerial dialogue. They also looked forward to the Global Entrepreneurship Summit in India in November, with Ivanka Trump leading the US delegation. President Trump welcomed the first shipment of American crude oil to India and pledged to be a reliable supplier of energy. Prime Minister Modi thanked President Trump for his leadership in uniting the world against North Korea.